  "user_line_comments": {
    "7245": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nLoads 20 level data files (\"CAVE01\" through \"CAVE20\") from disk into memory\nsequentially starting at $2000. It stores the starting address of each level\nin a lookup table for later access.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: table_level_start_addresses (word pointers), all_levels_end_addr\nSide Effects: Loads data from disk; Modifies memory from $2000 onwards.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7331": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nCopies the level data for the current level index into the buffer at $1300.\nThe routine switches to C128 Bank 1 to perform the copy.\n\nInputs:  current_level_index ($60D9)\nOutputs: Memory at $1300 (Bank 1) updated with level data\nSide Effects: Switches to Bank 1, modifies $FB-$FC, $FD-$FE, and $02-$03\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7415": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nConverts a binary number (1-20) in the Accumulator into two ASCII digits\nand stores them into the filename template \"CAVEXX\".\n\nInputs:  A = Level number\nOutputs: str_filename_template updated with ASCII digits\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7492": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nManages the sequence of events during state transitions (Game Over, Level End).\nUses a 16-bit countdown timer for delays and a table-driven sequencer for steps.\n\nInputs:  event_sequence_active, game_state, event_flags\nOutputs: game_state, event_timer_lo/hi, event_flags\nSide Effects: Resets game objects, triggers jumps to state handlers\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7653": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nAdvances the event sequence by loading the next command and delay from tables.\n\nInputs:  event_table_index, event_step_delay\nOutputs: event_current_value, event_step_delay\nSide Effects: Increments event_table_index\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7695": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDisables the in-game timer/power drain.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: Sets b_game_timer_active to 0\nSide Effects: Prevents the game timer from updating in update_game_timer\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7701": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nResets the SID chip registers to silence all voices.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Mutes SID hardware\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7738": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMain dispatcher for updating active sound effects. Calls update handlers for\n8 possible sound effect slots. Each handler checks its own status flag.\n\nInputs:  sound_effect_1_status .. sound_effect_8_status\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Modifies SID registers and internal SFX timers/state.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7762": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSilences all SID voices and resets sound effect status flags.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: sound_effect_*_status flags set to 0\nSide Effects: SID chip registers are reset (silenced)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7765": "",
    "7792": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMain gameplay logic handler. Orchestrates entity updates, collisions, and\nstate transitions when the game is in the active gameplay state (0) or\na specific secondary state (4).\n\nInputs:  gameplay_state, is_game_paused\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates player and entity states via subroutines.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7834": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nChecks for collision between the player and a fixed-address hazard/enemy.\nThe hazard's coordinates are at $77C3-$77C5.\n\nInputs:  player_x ($7AFB/C), player_y ($7AFD), hazard_x ($77C3/4), hazard_y ($77C5)\nOutputs: player_hit_flag ($3FA4) set to $FF on collision\nSide Effects: Jumps to player_hit_handler ($5056) if collision occurs\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7894": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nChecks if the player's laser hits the lamp in the current room.\nThe laser has a horizontal range of 50 pixels in the facing direction.\n\nInputs:  player_facing_direction ($7B01), player_x/y_pos, hazard_x/y_1\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Calls break_lamp_and_darken ($5056) if hit\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "7969": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nIterates through all active game objects and checks for collision with the\nplayer character using a per-object bounding box.\n\nInputs:  num_active_objects ($71E0), player_x/y, object_x/y tables\nOutputs: Jumps to handle_player_collision ($8185) on contact\nSide Effects: Calls get_object_hitbox to populate ZP hitbox bounds\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8125": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nChecks for collisions between the player and game entities (enemies/objects).\nUses dynamic bounds calculated by calculate_entity_collision_bounds.\nSkips non-collidable entities (type 4) and already-hit entities.\n\nInputs:  player_x_pos ($7AFD), player_y_pos_lo/hi ($7AFB/C)\nOutputs: Calls handle_collision_player_entity on hit\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8205": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nChecks for collisions between the player and game entities (v2).\nIncludes special handling for entity type 4 with larger bounds.\n\nInputs:  player_x_pos ($7AFD), player_y_pos_lo/hi ($7AFB/C)\nOutputs: entity_collision_flag,x ($71D1)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8298": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nLoads a file from disk to a specific memory address.\n\nInputs:  A = length of filename\n         X/Y = pointer to filename\n         $FB/$FC = destination address\nOutputs: X/Y = End address of loaded data + 1\n         C flag = set on error\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8301": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nLoads a file from the current device into memory.\n\nInputs:  .A = Filename length\n         .X = Filename pointer low\n         .Y = Filename pointer high\n         p_load_ptr_lo/hi ($FB/$FC) = Load destination address\n         zpa_BA ($BA) = Device number\nOutputs: .A = Error code (if any)\n         .X/.Y = End address of loaded data\n         C flag = Set on error\nSide Effects: Reads data from device into RAM\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8315": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSaves a block of memory to the current device.\n\nInputs:  .A = Filename length\n         .X = Filename pointer low\n         .Y = Filename pointer high\n         p_load_ptr_lo/hi ($FB/$FC) = Start address of block\n         zpa_FD/FE ($FD/$FE) = End address of block (+1)\n         zpa_BA ($BA) = Device number\nOutputs: .A = Error code (if any)\n         C flag = Set on error\nSide Effects: Writes data to device\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8332": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSends a command string to the disk drive command channel (SA 15).\nTypically used for scratching (deleting) files: \"S0:FILENAME\"\n\nInputs:  .A = Command length\n         .X = Command pointer low\n         .Y = Command pointer high\n         zpa_BA ($BA) = Device number\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Executes disk command\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8351": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nReads and displays (or prints) the disk drive error channel status.\n\nInputs:  zpa_BA ($BA) = Device number\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Reads from disk command channel\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8390": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nConfigures KERNAL Logical File 1 using the current device number.\nEnsures the device number is at least 8 (disk drive fallback).\n\nInputs:  Y = Secondary address (SA)\n         zpa_BA ($BA) = Current device number\nOutputs: None (Sets KERNAL LFS state)\nSide Effects: Calls KERNAL SETLFS ($FFBA)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8405": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nPerforms the initial system setup when launched from BASIC. Configures the \nC128 memory model (MMU), saves the OS zero page state, disables system \ninterrupts (CIA and NMI), and mutes the sound before jumping to the game's\nstate initialization.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: MMU set to Bank 0, OS Zero Page saved, CIA/NMI disabled, SID muted\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8437": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMain game loop dispatcher. Polls input, updates the game timer, and\ndispatches to the appropriate handler based on the current game state.\n\nInputs:  game_state\nOutputs: game_state_prev\nSide Effects: Calls input routines and state handlers.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8509": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDisables interrupts from both CIA chips and clears any pending flags.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: CIA interrupts disabled, interrupt status cleared\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8524": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes a custom raster interrupt handler. Configures the VIC-II\nto trigger at a specific line and sets up a register-saving wrapper\nthat jumps to the provided handler address. Also sets MMU to RAM Bank 0.\n\nInputs:  A = Raster line for initial interrupt\n         X = LSB of handler address\n         Y = MSB of handler address\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Disables/enables IRQs, hijacks hardware IRQ vector at $FFFE\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8572": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nHelper routine to chain to the next raster interrupt in a sequence.\nIt updates the trigger line and handler address, acknowledges the\ncurrent interrupt, and returns to the interrupted code.\n\nInputs:  A = Next raster line\n         X = LSB of next handler\n         Y = MSB of next handler\nOutputs: None (RTI)\nSide Effects: Restores A, X, Y registers\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8590": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nRestores the standard C128 KERNAL interrupt handler and the default\nMMU configuration ($0E). Disables any active VIC raster interrupts.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Disables VIC interrupts, restores RAM IRQ vector to $EA31\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8613": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMultiplies the accumulator by 5.\n\nInputs:  A = value to multiply\nOutputs: A = A * 5\nSide Effects: Overwrites $ED\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8620": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMultiplies the accumulator by 7.\n\nInputs:  A - Value to multiply\nOutputs: A - Result (A * 7)\nSide Effects: Modifies ZP $ED\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8629": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMultiplies the value in the Accumulator by 30.\n\nInputs:  A = value to multiply\nOutputs: A = result (A * 30)\nSide Effects: Modifies $ED\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "8642": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nFast approximation of division by 10 using shifts and additions.\nResult is A / 10.\n\nInputs:  A = value to divide\nOutputs: A = A / 10\nSide Effects: Overwrites $ED\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "13881": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSets the VIC-II chip to 25-line Standard Text Mode.\nPreserves Screen On/Off status and Extended Color Mode.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Modifies VIC Control Register 1 ($D011)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "13892": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nClears the 40-column text screen with spaces and fills color RAM.\n\nInputs:  Y = Color (0-15)\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Clears screen memory ($0400-$07E7) and sets color RAM ($D800-$DBE7).\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "13950": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDisables the VIC-II display at the bottom of the screen and restores the\nsystem IRQ handler. Used when transitioning out of the main game loop.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Disables VIC-II display (DEN=0), restores system IRQ.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "13976": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nWait for a specified number of video frames.\nEach frame is synchronized with raster line $FB.\n\nInputs:  X = Number of frames to wait\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Trashes A, X.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "13992": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUnpacks RLE-compressed screen data from p_load_ptr to p_save_end.\nAlso fills Color RAM (derived from p_save_end) with the specified color.\n\nInputs:  A = Color for the characters\n         p_load_ptr ($FB) = Source data pointer\n         p_save_end ($FD) = Destination screen pointer\nOutputs: p_load_ptr, p_save_end (advanced)\nSide Effects: Updates Screen RAM and Color RAM\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "14063": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nConverts a binary byte to a 3-digit decimal ASCII string.\nSupports leading zero suppression and copies the result to a buffer.\n\nInputs:  A = value to convert (0-255)\n         X = number of digits (usually 3)\n         p_save_end_lo/hi = destination buffer pointer\n         force_leading_zeros_flag = 0: suppress, !=0: keep zeros\nOutputs: (p_save_end_lo),y = resulting ASCII string\n         Y = updated buffer offset\nSide Effects: Modifies ascii_temp_buffer and num_digits ($FF)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "14094": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nConverts a BCD byte sequence to an ASCII string.\nSupports leading zero suppression and copies the result to a buffer.\n\nInputs:  X = number of digits to process\n         p_load_ptr_lo/hi = pointer to BCD bytes\n         p_save_end_lo/hi = destination buffer pointer\n         force_leading_zeros_flag = 0: suppress, !=0: keep zeros\nOutputs: (p_save_end_lo),y = resulting ASCII string\n         Y = updated buffer offset\nSide Effects: Modifies ascii_temp_buffer and num_digits ($FF)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "14171": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the message renderer state.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: message_finished_flag ($3758) = 0\n         message_column_index ($3759) = 0\n         message_timer ($375A) = 1\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "14185": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the message renderer, processing one character or command per tick.\nHandles special codes: $00 (End), $FF (Newline), $FE (Wait), $1E (Skip).\n\nInputs:  p_message_data ($F5) - Pointer to message data\n         p_message_screen ($F7) - Pointer to current screen row\nOutputs: message_finished_flag ($3758) set to $FF when done\nSide Effects: Updates screen memory, triggers sound effect\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "16002": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nPolls Joystick 2 and Paddle 1 to update the global input state.\nMaintains previous state in previous_event_flags for edge detection.\n\nInputs:  $DC00 (Joystick 2), $D419 (Paddle 1)\nOutputs: event_flags ($3E80), previous_event_flags ($3E81)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "16022": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMerges keyboard movement keys (I, J, K, L) and fire keys (Shift) into the\njoystick state. This allows controlling the character via either joystick\nin Port 2 or the keyboard.\n\nInputs:  input_state (current joystick state), keyboard row buffers\nOutputs: input_state (updated with keyboard bits)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "16152": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nScans selected rows of the keyboard matrix (0, 1, 4, 5, 6, 7).\nMaintains current and previous state for each row to allow edge detection.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: kb_row0_state through kb_row7_state\nSide Effects: Modifies CIA1 Port A ($DC00) and DDR ($DC02)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "16265": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nResets the state of monitored keyboard rows to inactive ($FF).\nThis effectively clears any currently detected key presses for rows 0, 1, 4, 5, 6, and 7.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: kb_row0_state, kb_row1_state, kb_row4_state, kb_row5_state, kb_row6_state, kb_row7_state = $FF\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "18889": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the level map data and pointer tables.\n\nInputs:  current_level_index ($60D9)\nOutputs: room_state_data ($E8B8), room_ptr_table ($E000)\nSide Effects: Calls init_room_entities, sets level parameters.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "18953": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the level state by setting lit colors from tables and generating\na room pointer table at $E000 from the raw level data at $1300.\nIt iterates through 96 potential rooms, skipping compressed room data.\n\nInputs:  X = Current level index\nOutputs: level_lit_color, level_multicolor_1, room table at $E000\nSide Effects: Calls disable_all_hazards, modifies ZP pointers\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "19056": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSkips one or more rows of compressed room data while advancing the data pointer.\nAlso identifies rooms containing a special marker ($D3), likely a checkpoint.\n\nInputs:  p_room_data_lo/hi (ptr), v_room_row_index, v_room_index\nOutputs: p_room_data_lo/hi (advanced), v_room_row_index, v_checkpoint_room_index\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "19126": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nHelper for room data scanning. Analyzes a single data byte to determine how\nmany tiles to advance the row offset. Also detects the special $D3 marker.\n\nInputs:  A (data byte), v_room_row_offset, v_room_index\nOutputs: v_room_row_offset (updated), v_checkpoint_room_index\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "19184": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes all game entities and state for the current room. This routine is\ncalled whenever the player transitions between rooms (left, right, up, down).\nIt resets hazard flags, calls specialized initialization routines for various\ngame systems, and fetches level data from a pointer table at $E000 indexed\nby the level number. If the room data starts with an EOF marker ($FF), it\nclears the playfield screen memory and disables sprites.\n\nInputs:  a_3F9E (Level index), hazard_active_1, a_7A73, a_82AB\nOutputs: a_3FA7, a_3FA8, a_3FA6 (State flags), zpa_02/03 (Room data pointer)\nSide Effects: Calls 8 init routines; Disables VIC-II sprites ($D015=0) if empty\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "19681": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDecompresses level data from (zpa_02) to (zpa_04) using a custom RLE-based \nformat with line templates and special attribute handling.\n\nInputs:  (zpa_02) level data ptr, (zpa_04) destination ptr, zpa_1E count\nOutputs: (zpa_02) updated ptr, (zpa_04) updated ptr, zpa_1E reaches 0\nSide Effects: Modifies $E340..$E367, zpa_06/07, zpa_1F, A, X, Y\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "19829": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDecompresses a single RLE-encoded packet from a level data stream into a\n40-column line buffer. Handles special cases for common background tile\nindices (0, 1, 2) and line-remainder fills.\n\nInputs:  (zpa_02) = compressed data pointer, (zpa_04) = dest pointer, zpa_1F = bytes remaining in line\nOutputs: Pointers and counter updated\nSide Effects: Writes to memory at (zpa_04)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "19991": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the level's visual state based on whether the \"lamp broken\" flag is\nset for the current level. If the lamp is broken, it blacks out large\nportions of the screen and sets the global tile color to black. If the lamp\nis lit, it restores the background/border characters and sets the tile\ncolor to white (15).\n\nInputs:  current_level_index ($3F9E)\nOutputs: lamp_broken_flag ($3FA4), dark_screen_color ($3FA3)\nSide Effects: Updates screen memory and tile color ($85E5)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "20002": "--- LIGHT MODE ---",
    "20046": "--- DARK MODE ---",
    "20090": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the current wall tile based on its 4-bit connectivity mask.\nSelects proper corner or edge characters by checking neighbors (U, L, R, D).\nAlso handles top-of-wall decoration for cells with no wall above.\n\nInputs:  X = Row index, Y = Column index, zpa_02/03 = Screen row pointer\nOutputs: Updated character at (zpa_02), Y\nSide Effects: May update character 2 rows above for top-of-wall caps.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "20405": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMain dispatcher for room objects with IDs 5 and greater. Maps object IDs from\nthe room data to their respective initialization or handler routines.\n\nInputs:  A = Object ID (5-255)\n         X = Entity index (usually 0)\n         Y = Object position index in room data\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Calls specific handlers for items, hazards, and entities.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "20644": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSets sprite multicolor registers and internal color variables to dark grey.\nThis is called when the player's lamp is broken to dim the sprites.\n\nInputs:  None (uses constant #$0b / Dark Grey)\nOutputs: $D025, $D026, $7F, $80, $91, and array at $710E\nSide Effects: Updates VIC-II sprite multicolor registers.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "20670": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the background color used for \"dark mode\" and triggers a hardware \nrefresh, but only if the lamp is actually broken.\n\nInputs:  A = New background color\n         lamp_broken_flag = Non-zero if lamp is broken\nOutputs: dark_screen_color = Updated with A if lamp is broken\nSide Effects: Updates VIC-II BG3 register ($D024) via jump to j_5069\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "20682": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nReads a character from the screen buffer at the specified pixel coordinates.\nThe play area is limited to 136 pixels vertically (17 rows).\n\nInputs:  A = Vertical pixel coordinate (0-135)\n         p_save_end (word) = Horizontal pixel coordinate (0-319)\nOutputs: A = Character code at the location, or 0 if out of bounds\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "20735": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the game statistics for a new game.\nClears current score, sets initial lives to 4, and initializes high score.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: score_lo/med/hi, lives, high_score_lo/med/hi, high_score_check_enabled\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "20783": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the current score by adding the score delta and checking for extra lives.\n\nInputs:  score_delta_lo/mid/hi ($50F8-50FA), current_score_lo/mid/hi ($50F4-50F6)\nOutputs: current_score_lo/mid/hi updated, score_delta cleared to 0\nSide Effects: Updates score UI, updates lives count and UI if threshold reached\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "20980": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the 6-digit score display at the bottom of the screen.\nUnpacks the 3-byte BCD score into 6 digits and renders them using a\ncustom 2-character-per-digit font.\n\nInputs:  score_lo, score_med, score_hi ($50F4-$50F6)\nOutputs: Screen RAM at $0788-$0793 updated\nSide Effects: Modifies screen RAM, level_counter ($FF), and bcd_unpacked_buf.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "21206": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nLoads the high score table from disk.\nIf loading fails or is first run, it initializes with defaults.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: High score table at $527F-$52C5 loaded from disk\nSide Effects: Modifies memory, uses KERNAL LOAD\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "21239": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSaves current high scores to the file \"HER-TOPSCORES\". It scratches the \nexisting file first to ensure the save succeeds on most CBM disk drives.\n\nInputs:  High scores in high_scores_table ($527F)\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Deletes and creates \"HER-TOPSCORES\" on disk.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "21286": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the high score table with default values.\n\nInputs:  Default scores from $5239\nOutputs: High score table at $527F-$52C5 updated\nSide Effects: Modifies memory\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "21307": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the high score table with the current score and level index.\nIf the score qualifies, it shifts lower entries down and inserts the new one.\n\nInputs:  score_lo, score_med, score_hi, current_level_index\nOutputs: A = index in table (0-9) if high score, or $FF if not.\nSide Effects: Modifies d_active_high_scores table.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "21451": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the zero-page pointer p_load_ptr ($FB/$FC) to point to the\nactive high score table at $527F. This buffer area is also reused for \nroom data and other dynamic game state.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: p_load_ptr points to $527F\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "21461": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDisables and resets all sprites. Clears positions and control registers.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Disables all sprites, clears VIC-II sprite registers ($D000-$D01D)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "21490": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the entity/sprite system arrays and hardware registers.\nSets up the initial identity mapping and resets all entity properties.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: $20..$32 = 0..18, $33..$45 = $FF, $92..$B7 = $00\nSide Effects: Enables multicolor for all 8 hardware sprites.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "23467": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDisables Non-Maskable Interrupts (NMI) by pointing the hardware vector\nto a dummy handler that simply returns. This prevents the Restore key\nor other NMI sources from interrupting the game.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Overwrites NMI vector at $FFFA/$FFFB\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "23479": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSaves the contents of the Zero Page into a backup buffer.\nThis is used to store the current ZP context (likely for disk I/O or level\nmanagement) into the buffer at $5AB3. Addresses $03 to $FA are saved.\n\nInputs:  Zero Page ($03-$FA)\nOutputs: Buffer at $5AB3\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "23492": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nRestores the contents of the Zero Page from a backup buffer.\nThis is used to swap in a specific ZP context (likely for disk I/O or level\nmanagement) from the buffer at $5AB3. Addresses $03 to $FA are updated.\n\nInputs:  Buffer at $5AB3\nOutputs: Zero Page ($03-$FA)\nSide Effects: Overwrites a large portion of the Zero Page.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "23666": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nHandles high score name entry using a joystick. Displays a blinking cursor\nat the specified (X, Y) coordinates. The user selects characters by pushing\nUp/Down and confirms with the Fire button. Any keyboard press will also\nterminate input.\n\nInputs:  A = Maximum name length\n         X = Screen column (0-39)\n         Y = Screen row (0-24)\nOutputs: f_input_buffer = Null-terminated name string\nSide Effects: Writes characters to screen memory ($0400-$07E7)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "23748": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nProcesses keyboard input for the text entry screen.\nHandles key debouncing, buffer management, and special keys (Backspace, Enter).\nUpdates the screen in real-time as characters are typed.\n\nInputs:  A = Key code from keyboard scan routine.\nOutputs: Updates input buffer and cursor state.\nSide Effects: Updates screen memory.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "23816": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nScans the 8x8 keyboard matrix and returns a value from the translation table.\n\nInputs:  None (scans CIA1 hardware)\nOutputs: A = character code from table, or 0 if no key pressed\nSide Effects: Modifies CIA1 $DC00/DC02, uses ZP $FB-$FC, $FF\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "23892": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nHandles joystick input for the name entry screen. Processes directional\ninput (Up/Down) to cycle through the alphabet table, the Fire button to\nselect the current character, and the Left button to delete the last character.\n\nInputs:  None (reads input_state and previous_event_flags)\nOutputs: Updates buf_entered_name and name entry state variables\nSide Effects: Updates screen memory to show selected/deleted characters\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "24044": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the visual blinking of the input cursor or selected character.\nAlternates between a space and either the default cursor ($1E) or the\ncurrently selected character from the input table.\n\nInputs:  a_input_blink_cnt, a_input_char_idx, a_input_cursor_x, a_input_cursor_y\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Draws character to screen memory via s_draw_char_at_cursor\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "24063": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDraws a character at the current name-entry cursor position on the screen.\nCalculates the screen address based on a_input_cursor_x and a_input_cursor_y.\n\nInputs:  A = Character screencode to draw\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Modifies screen memory at $0400 + (row * 40) + col\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "24100": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDeletes the last character entered in the name entry buffer.\nMoves the cursor position left and clears the characters on screen.\n\nInputs:  None (reads v_name_curr_len and v_name_cursor_x_pos)\nOutputs: Decrements v_name_curr_len and v_name_cursor_x_pos\nSide Effects: Updates screen memory to clear characters\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "25271": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the Game HUD (Heads-Up Display) during level startup.\nUnpacks RLE-encoded labels (SCORE, LIVES, LEVEL, etc.) to screen memory,\ndraws icons for miners to rescue, and resets numerical UI components.\n\nInputs:  current_level_index, miners_to_rescue_count\nOutputs: Screen memory ($0400-$07E7), several state tables (f_DB25, f_DB88)\nSide Effects: Updates the terminal screen to show the game UI.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "25417": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDraws the status icons representing miners remaining to be rescued.\nIcons are 1x2 characters, spaced every 2 columns at row 19/20.\n\nInputs:  miners_to_rescue_count ($7B06)\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates screen memory at $0711 and $0739\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "25439": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nErases a single dynamite icon from the UI status bar.\nCalled when a dynamite stick is used or lost.\n\nInputs:  v_dynamite_count (the current number of sticks)\nOutputs: v_dynamite_count (decremented by the caller after return)\nSide Effects: Clears two characters on the screen at rows 19 and 20.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "25455": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the level number display in the UI status bar.\nCalculates whether the level (1-indexed) is 1 or 2 digits and sets the\nscreen destination address before jumping to the BCD conversion routine.\n\nInputs:  current_level_index (0-indexed)\nOutputs: p_save_end ($077C), level_counter (1 or 2)\nSide Effects: Jumps to BCD conversion and display routine at $6413.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "25650": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUnpacks nibbles from a source buffer and displays them on screen using\na custom 2-character-wide digit font.\n\nInputs:\n  X: Number of digits to process\n  p_load_ptr: Source buffer (e.g., BCD score)\n  p_save_end: Screen destination address\nOutputs:\n  Digits displayed on screen at p_save_end\nSide Effects:\n  Modifies level_counter, bcd_unpacked_buf, X, Y, A.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "25722": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nOrchestrates the per-frame game logic updates, including entities, hazards,\nplayer collisions, and final entity depth sorting.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates entity positions/states, hazard states, and sorts entity list.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "26287": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes and displays sprites 0 through 6 for the title screen.\nSets X positions, colors, and data pointers, then enables expansion\nfor sprites 0 and 1.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: Modifies VIC-II sprite registers and sprite pointers ($07F8)\nSide Effects: Disables all sprites first, then re-enables 0-6.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "26376": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the vertical positions of sprites 0-6 during the title screen\nintro animation. Sprites 0-2 move down from the top, while sprites 4-6\nmove up from the top (wrapping around to the bottom).\n\nInputs:  title_anim_offset (current vertical displacement)\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates Sprite 0-6 Y-position hardware registers ($D001-$D00D)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "27102": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDraws a 24x7 character and color block to the center of the screen.\nCommonly used for game screens (e.g., logo or status messages).\n\nInputs:  None (Uses hardcoded source addresses $680E and $68B6)\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates Screen memory at $0430 and Color RAM at $D830.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "27205": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSets the color for a 40-column menu item row in the Color RAM.\nMenu items start at row 11 ($D9B8) and are spaced every two rows (80 bytes).\n\nInputs:  X = Color value (0-15)\n         Y = Menu item index (row = 11 + Y * 2)\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates 40 bytes of Color RAM starting at $D9B8 + (Y * 80)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "27480": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the Dynamite control instruction message on the screen.\nCycles through different control methods (Joystick Down, Double Down, Space, 2nd Fire).\n\nInputs:  dynamite_control_index ($60D7) - index (0-3) of the message to display.\nOutputs: None (modifies screen memory at $060D).\nSide Effects: Updates 30 characters of screen memory.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "27502": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the depth/zone range text in the UI based on the current selection.\nThis copies a 5-byte string (e.g., \\\"05-08\\\") to the screen status area.\n\nInputs:  v_selected_zone_index (byte index into t_zone_range_strings)\nOutputs: v_ui_zone_range_pos (5 bytes written to screen RAM)\nSide Effects: Updates display of current zone range in the menu or status bar.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28008": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nPrepares and displays the high score table on the VIC-II text screen.\nUnpacks title and headers, then iterates 10 times to display each entry:\nRank string, Score (BCD), Level, and Initials.\n\nInputs:  None (uses global high score data)\nOutputs: Screen memory starting at $0437\nSide Effects: Updates VIC-II text screen memory\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28339": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nClears the screen, displays a \\\"RESETTING RANKING...\\\" message, initializes the\nhigh score table with default values, and saves it to disk.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Disables interrupts/display, clears screen, updates disk file.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28381": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nClears the screen, displays a \\\"SAVING DATA...\\\" message, and saves the current\nhigh score table to disk. Used during game exit or manual save.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Disables interrupts/display, clears screen, updates disk file.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28431": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the screen flash state machine. This effect is used during\ndynamite explosions and miner rescues.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: v_screen_flash_state = 0 (Idle)\n         zpa_82 = 7 (Unknown purpose, possibly initial dynamite count)\nSide Effects: Resets any active screen flash effect.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28441": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the state and animation of the player's dynamite.\nHandles three states:\n1. Placed: Countdown timer and sprite frame cycling ($A1-$A4).\n2. Exploding: Background color cycling and final sprite frame ($A5).\n3. Wait: Final delay before disappearing.\n\nInputs:  v_dynamite_state, v_dynamite_timer, v_dynamite_anim_timer\nOutputs: v_dynamite_state, v_dynamite_timer, v_dynamite_anim_timer, v_dynamite_frame, v_dynamite_bg_color\nSide Effects: Updates background color ($D021) during explosion.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28551": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the explosion effect sequence. Typically called when the\ndynamite fuse timer reaches zero. It sets up the animation state,\ninitial color, and triggers the sound effect.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: v_screen_flash_state, v_screen_flash_anim_frame, v_screen_flash_timer\nSide Effects: Triggers sound effect via v_sfx_slot_1_status\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28578": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nIterates through the list of active objects and checks for a collision\nwith the point defined by (collision_point_x, collision_point_y).\nIf a collision is found, it jumps to the collision handler at $875A.\n\nInputs:  collision_point_x, collision_point_y_lo/hi\nOutputs: None (jumps to $875A on collision)\nSide Effects: May destroy an object via the handler at $875A\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28687": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the \\\"special object\\\" slot with the Miner's state and coordinates.\nCalled during room loading to place the trapped miner at their fixed position.\n\nInputs:  X = Index into room coordinate tables\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Sets special_obj_state to 3, updates positions and sprite.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28734": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the dynamite drop sequence. Records the player's current position \nas the explosion center and starts the fuse countdown timer.\n\nInputs:  player_x_pos, player_y_pos_lo/hi\nOutputs: v_screen_flash_state = 1, v_screen_flash_timer = 30, \n         collision_point_x/y = player_x/y\nSide Effects: Triggers sound effect 2 and updates dark mode color if lamp broken.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "28783": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSynchronizes the screen flash / explosion entity (index 3) coordinates and\nanimation frame with the current collision point. If no flash is active,\nthe entity is moved off-screen.\n\nInputs:  v_screen_flash_state, collision_point_x/y, v_screen_flash_anim_frame\nOutputs: v_entity_y[3], v_entity_x[3], v_entity_y_hi[3], v_entity_ptr_lo[3]\nSide Effects: Updates entity table used for sprite rendering.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "29197": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nResets the active entity count to zero. Called during room transitions to\nclear the previous room's state.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: num_entities = 0\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "29203": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nAdds a new entity to the active list and initializes its state.\nPreserves the caller's X and Y registers.\n\nInputs:  A (Entity Type), X/Y (Preserved context)\nOutputs: num_entities incremented\nSide Effects: Calls spawn_entity\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "29221": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes and spawns a new entity into the game world.\n\nSets the entity's type, calculates its initial pixel position based on\nthe level grid coordinates, and initializes type-specific attributes\nsuch as sprite frames, timers, and persistent state flags.\n\nInputs:\n  A: Entity type\n  X: Entity slot index\n  item_count ($1E): Column in the level grid\n  line_byte_count ($1F): Row in the level grid\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Modifies the entity property arrays for the given slot index.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "29605": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMain entity update loop. Iterates through all active game entities (enemies,\nhazards, etc.) and calls the per-entity update logic.\n\nInputs:  num_entities ($71E0)\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates all active entities' state, including motion and timers.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "29618": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates logic for a single entity. Handles the \"hit\" state timer (transitioning\nfrom hit to dead state) or dispatches to type-specific movement handlers.\n\nInputs:  X = Entity index (0-indexed)\nOutputs: Updates entity_hit_flag, entity_timer, and entity positions.\nSide Effects: Calls specific movement routines for different entity types.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "29679": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates an entity's horizontal position by adding an oscillating offset.\nThe oscillation follows a 16-step triangular pattern and updates every 4 frames.\n\nInputs:  X = Entity index\nOutputs: entity_x_pos,x (updated)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "29721": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates an entity's 2D position and velocity to seek a target coordinate.\nThe routine uses 24-bit precision for Y and 16-bit for X.\nVelocity is adjusted based on whether the current position is above or below\nthe target, creating a \\\"hovering\\\" or \\\"seeking\\\" effect.\n\nInputs:  X = Entity index\nOutputs: Updated entity state (position and velocity)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "29885": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMoves the current entity vertically towards the player's position.\nThe movement is 0.5 pixels per call. Collision is checked at the target\nY position (offset by -9 or +6 pixels) using the entity's X position.\n\nInputs:  X (entity index), player_y_pos, entity_y_pos, entity_y_pos_frac\nOutputs: entity_y_pos, entity_y_pos_frac, p_save_end (temp)\nSide Effects: Calls get_char_at_pixel\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30397": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nCalculates entity-specific collision bounding box thresholds.\nSets horizontal and vertical distance limits based on entity type and player direction.\n\nInputs:  X = entity index, entity_type,x, player_facing_direction\nOutputs: p_room_data_lo/hi (X bounds), dest_ptr_lo/hi (Y bounds)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30552": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nIterates through all active entities and processes those that have triggered\na collision. Marks them as \"hit\" and updates persistent room data.\n\nInputs:  num_entities, entity_collision_flag\nOutputs: entity_hit_flag (set to $02)\nSide Effects: Updates persistent data to prevent entity reappearance.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30575": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMarks an entity as inactive (destroyed/collected) in persistent storage.\nThis prevents the entity from respawning when re-entering the room.\n\nInputs:  X = Entity index, level_index_for_lamp = Current level index\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Modifies persistent data buffer for current level.\nReuses $1C-$1D as pointer.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30662": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDisables the primary hazard (hazard 1) by clearing its active status flag.\nUsed during entity initialization and room changes to ensure the hazard is\ndeactivated until specifically spawned.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: hazard_active_1 ($77C2) = $00\nSide Effects: Disables hazard update and collision checks for this slot.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30668": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes and enables hazard 1 at a specific grid position.\nCalculates pixel coordinates from grid coordinates (X=row, Y=col).\n\nInputs:  X = Grid Row, Y = Grid Column\nOutputs: hazard_active_1 ($77C2) = $FF\nSide Effects: Sets hazard position; restores X and Y on exit.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30781": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the player's state at the start of a level or after losing a life.\nDisables the backpack/helicopter and resets the energy level.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: player_collision_enable = 0 (Backpack inactive)\n         zpa_81 = 10 (Initial energy units?)\n         zpa_A7 = 255 (Initial energy sub-units?)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30795": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMain player collision processing routine. Checks for contact with enemies,\nprojectiles, and the ceiling, then updates animation timers.\n\nInputs:  player_x_pos, player_y_pos, player_facing_direction\nOutputs: player_collision_hit_type (0=none, 1=partial, 2=solid)\nSide Effects: Jumps to lethal collision handler if hit detected.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30807": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nCalculates distance to nearest object/boundary in player's facing direction.\nUsed to determine laser beam length and collision area.\n\nInputs:  player_facing_direction, player_x_pos, player_y_pos, object arrays\nOutputs: laser_proximity_status ($7828)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30939": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates frame counters for player collision animations.\nCycles through 6 phases (2 ticks hi, 3 ticks lo).\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: collision_anim_frame_lo, collision_anim_frame_hi\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "30970": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nActivates the player's helicopter backpack when the fire button is released.\nResets the propeller animation counters and starts the backpack sound.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: is_backpack_active ($7827), propeller_anim_frame ($7829), \n         propeller_anim_tick ($782A), sound_effect_3_status ($8A00)\nSide Effects: Resets animation and starts sound effect.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31008": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the position, animation frame, and visibility of the player's\nlaser beam entity based on backpack state, direction, and reach.\n\nInputs:  is_backpack_active, player_x_pos, v_entity_x, v_entity_x_hi,\n         v_entity_y, player_facing_direction, laser_proximity_status,\n         laser_anim_frame\nOutputs: laser_y_pos, laser_x_lo, laser_x_hi, laser_frame_index,\n         laser_visibility_flag\nSide Effects: Positions and prepares the laser sprite/entity for rendering.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31149": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nPer-pixel (or per-tile) collision detection for the player sprite (helicopter).\nThis is a highly optimized, unrolled block of code that checks multiple\npoints around the player's position against the tilemap.\n\nInputs:  Y (index/offset), ($B0) (tilemap pointer)\nOutputs: None (branches to collision handler if hit)\nSide Effects: Jumps to collision handler labels (e.g., $7964)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31255": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the line animation counters.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: v_line_anim_frame_index = 0, v_line_anim_delay_counter = 0\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31264": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nAnimates a 40-character row of lava (row 16) with an 8-frame cycle.\n\nUpdates the screen row starting at $0680. Each frame consists of 20 bytes\nwhich are mirrored horizontally to create a 40-column effect. The animation\nadvances every 5 frames when the lava flag is active.\n\nInputs:  attr_expanded_flag ($3FA6), v_lava_anim_frame, v_lava_anim_delay\nOutputs: Screen memory at $0680–$06A7\nSide Effects: Updates animation counters and modifies screen row 16.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31352": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDisables the lava floor hazard by clearing its active flag.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: v_lava_hazard_active = 0\nSide Effects: Prevents lava collision and rendering.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31358": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nEnables and initializes the lava floor hazard at specified char coordinates.\nCalculates pixel positions and selects appropriate character codes based on\nthe hazard's vertical position on the screen.\n\nInputs:  X = Character X coordinate, Y = Character Y coordinate\nOutputs: v_lava_hazard_active = $FF, v_lava_x_pos, v_lava_y_pos_lo/hi,\n         v_lava_char_code updated.\nSide Effects: Configures the lava hazard for the current room.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31439": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nPrepares collision detection and rendering parameters for the lava floor hazard.\nUpdates zero-page variables with the current hazard position and character data\nif the hazard is active and not globally disabled.\n\nInputs:  v_lava_hazard_active, v_lava_y_pos_lo/hi, v_lava_x_pos, v_lava_char_code\nOutputs: zpa_58, zpa_6B (Y-pos), a_0045 (X-pos), zpa_7E (Char), a_0091 (Type ID)\nSide Effects: Updates shared hazard parameter ZP variables.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31515": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the player's position and state when entering a room or respawning.\nCalled when the \"Player Spawn\" entity (ID $0B) is encountered.\n\nInputs:  X = initial item count, Y = initial vertical tile-row position\nOutputs: player_y_pos, player_x_pos, player_facing_direction\nSide Effects: Unpauses the game, sets gameplay state to 1\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31592": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nResets gameplay state to 1 and places the player at X position 240.\nUsed during room entry or player respawn.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31643": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nMain gameplay logic dispatcher.\nRoutes execution to the appropriate state handler based on 'gameplay_state'.\nHandles active gameplay, intro animations, 'Ready' screen, and level transitions.\n\nInputs:  gameplay_state ($7AFA)\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates gameplay_state during transitions or input detection.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31747": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nHandles core gameplay updates including hazard collision, backpack thrust,\nand dynamite usage based on player input and current game state.\n\nInputs:  input_state ($3E80), gameplay_state ($7AFA), v_dynamite_count ($7B00)\nOutputs: Updated player state and equipment flags\nSide Effects: Triggers sound effects, HUD updates, and death sequences\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31813": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nHandles the logic for dropping a stick of dynamite.\nDecrements the inventory, spawns the dynamite object, and initializes the fuse.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: v_dynamite_count (decremented), v_dynamite_beep_delay (set)\nSide Effects: Updates UI, plays sound effect 6 (fuse beep)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31848": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the timing of the dynamite beep sound effect based on the remaining\nfuse time. As the fuse burns (counting up to 46), the beep delay decreases\nfrom 5 to 1, causing the beeps to accelerate as detonation approaches.\n\nInputs:  v_dynamite_fuse_timer ($7B04)\nOutputs: v_dynamite_beep_delay ($7B0C)\nSide Effects: Triggers sound effect 6 (beep) if not already playing.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31876": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nHandles player movement input and state updates.\nIf v_is_horizontal_mode is zero, it implements grid-aligned vertical movement\n(climbing) using the Left/Right buttons. Otherwise, it updates facing direction.\n\nInputs:  input_state ($3E80), v_is_horizontal_mode ($7B05)\nOutputs: player_y_pos_lo/hi, player_facing_direction, player_y_move_state\nSide Effects: Updates player animation and checks for floor/ceiling collisions.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "31969": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nProcesses vertical movement for the player, including coordinate updates,\nanimation frame management, collision detection with background tiles, and\nhandling screen transitions at the upper and lower boundaries.\n\nInputs:  player_y_pos_lo/hi, player_y_dir (1=Up, 2=Down)\nOutputs: player_y_pos_lo/hi updated, player_y_pos_prev_lo, animation state updated\nSide Effects: May trigger a room transition if boundary reached.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "32293": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the player's vertical position based on backpack thrust and gravity.\nWhen the Up button is held, the player accelerates upwards (negative velocity).\nWhen released, gravity takes over and the player accelerates downwards.\nA transition timer provides smooth momentum changes.\n\nInputs:  input_state ($3E80) - Bit 0: Up joystick button\nOutputs: player_y_pos_8bit ($7AFD), v_player_vertical_velocity ($7B02)\nSide Effects: Updates v_backpack_momentum_timer ($7B04)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "32468": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nChecks for horizontal collisions at a specific X coordinate.\nTests three Y positions (top, middle, bottom) against background tiles.\nHandles lethal tiles (kill) and solid tiles (push back/stop).\n\nInputs:  X = X coordinate to check\n         A = X coordinate to check (transferred from X)\n         player_y_pos = Player's current vertical position\nOutputs: v_dynamite_active_flag ($7B03) = 0 if blocked, $FF if clear\nSide Effects: Adjusts player_x_pos if a wall is hit.\n              Triggers handle_player_collision if a lethal tile is hit.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "32610": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nChecks for collision with the elevator object. If the player is within range,\nit docks them to the elevator, disabling dynamite and vertical movement.\n\nInputs:  player_x_pos, player_y_pos_lo/hi, a_82AB (Active flag), a_82AE (X), a_82AC/AD (Y)\nOutputs: player_x_pos, player_y_move_state, v_is_horizontal_mode_active\nSide Effects: Disables dynamite; Aligns player Y when undocking\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "32701": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nChecks if the player has collided with the active lava hazard.\n\nInputs:  player_x_pos, player_y_pos_lo/hi, v_lava_x_pos, v_lava_y_pos_lo/hi\nOutputs: gameplay_state (set to 3 on collision), player_y_move_state\nSide Effects: Updates lava char code, score, and deactivates backpack\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "32787": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSnaps the player's Y position to the nearest 8-pixel grid boundary.\nUses rounding (adds 4 pixels) before masking to find the closest tile edge.\n\nInputs:  player_y_pos_lo, player_y_pos_hi\nOutputs: player_y_pos_lo, player_y_pos_hi, player_y_target_aligned\nSide Effects: Updates player's vertical alignment.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "32810": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nPolls input to determine if the player wants to drop a dynamite stick.\nSupports multiple control modes (Joystick, Keyboard, Timed).\n\nInputs:  input_state, previous_event_flags, dynamite_control_index\nOutputs: A = $FF (Drop), $00 (Do nothing)\nSide Effects: Updates v_player_action_delay and v_dynamite_input_timeout\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "32979": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the dynamite beep timer and fuse animation counter.\nUsed during gameplay and intro/wait states to animate the dynamite fuse.\n\nInputs:  v_dynamite_beep_delay ($7B0C)\nOutputs: v_dynamite_beep_timer ($7B0B), v_dynamite_fuse_counter ($7B0A)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33090": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the player's sprite frame pointer based on the current game state,\nmovement, and animation frame.\n\nInputs:\n- gameplay_state: Current state (0-3: active, 4+: dying/collision)\n- v_dynamite_active_flag: Non-zero if player is using dynamite\n- player_facing_direction: 0 for Right, 1 for Left\n- player_y_move_state: 0=ground, 1=ascending, 2=descending\n- player_anim_frame: Frame index for walking/vertical animation\n\nOutputs:\n- v_player_sprite_frame: Updated sprite frame index\n\nSide Effects: None (updates memory variable used by sprite engine)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33352": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the player's power level and consumption rate for a new level.\nSets power to 128 ($80) and loads the decrement rate from a lookup table.\n\nInputs:  current_level_index (Level number)\nOutputs: current_power ($80), power_fraction ($0000), \n         power_consumption_rate (From table)\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33383": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the player's energy/power meter. Decrements power based on a fractional\naccumulation (depletion rate) and updates the segmented status bar display.\nTriggers a power-out event (collision/death) when energy reaches zero.\n\nInputs:  player_power, power_fraction_lo/hi, power_depletion_lo/hi\nOutputs: Updated player_power and visual status bar\nSide Effects: Calls handle_player_collision when power hits zero\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33422": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the power meter bar in the HUD based on the current power level.\nThe power level is divided by 4 to find the segment index, and the remainder\ndetermines the partial segment character ($5A-$5D).\n\nInputs:  v_power_level ($821B) - Current power remaining (0-127)\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates screen memory at v_hud_power_bar ($06D7)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33440": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the HUD power bar to the maximum level.\n\nFills the 32-character screen area for the power bar with the \\\"full\\\"\nblock character ($5E).\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Fills 32 characters starting at v_ui_power_bar_pos with $5E\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33456": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDeactivates the elevator by clearing the active flag.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: v_elevator_active = 0\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33462": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes the elevator at a specific tile position and sets its initial\ndirection based on its Y position.\n\nInputs:  X = Tile Column, Y = Tile Row\nOutputs: v_elevator_active = $FF, v_elevator_x, v_elevator_y_lo/hi\nSide Effects: Sets v_elevator_direction (1=Up, 2=Down)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33530": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nHandles the elevator movement and player positioning while on it. Checks for\ncollisions to change direction.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: Updates v_elevator_y_lo/hi, player_y_pos_lo/hi, p_save_end_lo/hi\nSide Effects: Toggles v_elevator_direction upon reaching boundaries\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33915": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDisables the moving wall hazard by clearing its active flag. This prevents\nthe update and collision routines from processing the wall.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: moving_wall_active ($83A2) set to 0\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33921": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nInitializes a moving wall hazard at the specified character coordinates.\nCalculates collision boundaries and sets the initial animation frame.\n\nInputs:  X = Row (0-24), Y = Column (0-39)\nOutputs: moving_wall_active, moving_wall_x, moving_wall_y_lo/hi\nSide Effects: Sets moving_wall_active to $FF\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "33992": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the moving wall animation by incrementing a delay timer and\nadvancing to the next frame in the ping-pong sequence table.\n\nInputs:  moving_wall_active, moving_wall_timer, moving_wall_frame_idx\nOutputs: moving_wall_frame, moving_wall_timer, moving_wall_frame_idx\nSide Effects: Calls refresh_moving_wall when the frame changes.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "34036": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nRefreshes the moving wall (barrier) on the screen.\n\nIf the wall is active, it clears the corresponding Color RAM region to Red\nand draws the current animation frame of the wall to Screen Memory.\nThe wall is an 8x6 staggered structure.\n\nInputs:\n  moving_wall_active ($83A2): Visibility flag\n  moving_wall_row ($83A7): Screen row (0-24)\n  moving_wall_col ($83A6): Screen column (0-39)\n  moving_wall_frame ($83A8): Animation frame index\n\nOutputs:\n  Screen Memory: Character indices updated\n  Color RAM: Colors updated to Red (2)\n\nSide Effects:\n  None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "34230": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDisables the moving wall hazard if it is currently active.\nResets the animation frame and redraws the wall in its inactive state.\n\nInputs:  moving_wall_active ($83A2)\nOutputs: moving_wall_active, moving_wall_frame ($83A3) set to 0\nSide Effects: Calls s_draw_moving_wall to update the screen.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "34278": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nResets the count of active objects in the current room to zero.\nThis is typically called during room initialization or when clearing the\nscreen of level-specific entities (monsters, items, etc).\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: num_active_objects ($85E4) is set to 0\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "34380": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nIterates through a list of up to 3 interactive objects and draws them if active.\n\nInputs:  v_object_count, v_object_status, v_object_row, v_object_col, v_object_state\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Modifies Screen RAM and Color RAM\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "34398": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nRenders a game object (like a breakable wall or laser barrier) at its screen\nposition. It draws either an intact 2x5 block or a destroyed 2x2 block based\non the object's state flag.\n\nInputs:  X = Object index\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Updates Screen and Color RAM. Modifies zero-page pointers $FB-$FE.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "34897": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nDraws a magma wall (vertical obstacle) on the screen.\n\nInputs:  X = entity index. Uses object_y_row_index, object_x_col_index,\n         and object_destroyed_flag.\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Modifies screen memory and triggers sound effect 8.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "35054": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates Sound Effect Slot 1 (Voice 3). Plays a short low-frequency noise\nburst (impact/hit sound) using a state machine with a 2-frame delay and\n3-frame duration.\n\nInputs:  v_sfx_slot_1_status (1 to start), v_sfx_slot_1_timer\nOutputs: v_sfx_slot_1_status (resets to 0 when done)\nSide Effects: Modifies SID Voice 3 registers ($D40E, $D40F, $D412-$D414)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "35138": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the dynamite fuse sound effect (Voice 3). Plays a continuous high-pitched\nnoise after a 2-frame initialization delay.\n\nInputs:  v_dynamite_fuse_sfx_status (35136)\nOutputs: v_dynamite_fuse_sfx_status, v_dynamite_fuse_sfx_timer\nSide Effects: Modifies SID Voice 3 (Freq=$3000, AD=$61, SR=$10, Wave=Noise)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "35218": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the helicopter backpack sound effect (SFX slot 3) using SID Voice 2.\nPlays a looping rising pitch sequence by cycling through a frequency table.\nHandles initialization (status 1) and graceful termination (status 3).\n\nInputs:  backpack_sfx_status, backpack_sfx_timer, backpack_sfx_freq_table\nOutputs: backpack_sfx_status, backpack_sfx_timer\nSide Effects: Modifies SID Voice 2 registers ($D407-$D40D)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "35330": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nSignals the helicopter backpack sound effect to stop.\nIf the sound is currently playing (status 2), it transitions to status 3,\nallowing the update routine to finish the current pitch cycle before stopping.\n\nInputs:  backpack_sfx_status\nOutputs: backpack_sfx_status\nSide Effects: None (logic handles SID cleanup in the update routine)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "35365": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates Sound Effect Slot 4 (Voice 1).\nThis sound effect consists of 15 steps of 4 frames each.\nEach step cycles through a 4-byte frequency and pulse width table,\ncreating a rapid rhythmic or oscillating effect.\n\nInputs:  sound_effect_4_status, sfx_4_frame_counter, sfx_4_step_index\nOutputs: sound_effect_4_status (updated)\nSide Effects: Modifies SID Voice 1 registers ($D400-$D406)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "35487": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the helicopter motor sound effect.\nIt plays a noise sound whose frequency is controlled by the player's power level.\nAs power decreases, the pitch of the motor noise also decreases.\n\nInputs:  v_helicopter_sound_status ($8A9D), v_power_level ($821B)\nOutputs: v_helicopter_sound_status ($8A9D), v_helicopter_sound_timer ($8A9E)\nSide Effects: Modifies SID Voice 1 registers\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "35570": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nProcesses the dynamite beep sound effect (Slot 6) using SID Voice 1.\nThis routine implements a pulsed noise sound. It is typically triggered\nas a one-shot by setting the status to 1. The beep consists of a 4-frame\nnoise burst followed by a 2-frame silence before resetting or stopping.\n\nInputs:  v_dynamite_beep_sfx_status ($8AF0)\nOutputs: v_dynamite_beep_sfx_status, v_dynamite_beep_sfx_timer ($8AF1)\nSide Effects: Updates SID Voice 1 registers ($D400-$D406)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "35681": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nRequests the dynamite beep sound effect to stop. If a beep is currently\nplaying (status 2), it transitions to status 3, which allows the current\n4-frame pulse to finish before silencing the voice and clearing the status.\n\nInputs:  v_dynamite_beep_sfx_status ($8AF0)\nOutputs: v_dynamite_beep_sfx_status\nSide Effects: None\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "35704": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nUpdates the state machine for sound effect slot 7 (Voice 1).\nHandles a short (1-frame) pulse waveform blip after a short delay.\n\nInputs:  sound_effect_7_status, sound_effect_7_timer\nOutputs: sound_effect_7_status, sound_effect_7_timer\nSide Effects: Modifies SID Voice 1 hardware registers ($D400-$D406)\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-"
  },
